This paper discusses side-channel attacks and proposes a mechanism for partitioning caches to selectively apply side-channel-resilient behavior only for isolated execution domains. This topic is closely related to computer security (cs.CR), computer architecture (cs.AR), software engineering (cs.SE), and system-level design and implementation (cs.SY, cs.DC).
